resturant1.description: Cozy, laid back atmosphere in a central location with 20 beers on tap, many of them brewed onsite. Limited (but inexpensive) food options to go with the beer.
resturant1.name: Crowbar & Bryggeri

resturant10.description: Great meat, good atmosphere, reasonable prices. If you are looking for a good place to eat steak in Oslo, look no further.
resturant10.name: Trancher Entrecôte

resturant11.description: Classic North Indian dishes served in established restaurant, with carved screens & traditional art.
resturant11.name: New Anarkali

resturant2.description: Late-opening, cozy, dark wood bar/restaurant with outdoor area, for burgers, burritos & BBQ dishes.
resturant2.name: Cafe Sara

resturant4.description: Want a burrito or salad bowl look no further than here! Great price for a filling and delicious burrito! They also have beer here! It's a busy spot but very much recommended!
resturant4.name: Freddy Fuego Burrito Bar

resturant5.description: Best pho in town! Great cozy restaurant with great variety within Vietnamese / Asian food.
resturant5.name: Dalat cafe Tran

resturant6.description: This place is a gem when it comes to cheap and good fast-food. The portion is big, and the meals are relatively cheap.
resturant6.name: Grytelokket Avd. Storgata

resturant7.description: Very good sushi and very reasonably priced compared to other sushi restaurants
resturant7.name: Sea Sushi Bar AS

resturant8.description: Relaxed restaurant with wooden furniture & stripped floors, for classic & modern Spanish tapas.
resturant8.name: Delicatessen Grünerløkka

resturant9.description: Nice pub in an old beer cellar. Serves beers that they brew themselves , together with an very good beer selection from others.
resturant9.name: Schouskjelleren Mikrobryggeri
